  "successor_acceptance": {
    "rules": [
      "Construct each cache signature centrally from the exact canonical inputs consumed by the result it protects, including output-affecting identity and assignment fields.",
      "Separate logical-analysis, downstream support/solid, execution-policy and presentation signatures so a change invalidates only its true dependency cone.",
      "Either calculate and return from the same declared quantised canonical values or hash the exact consumed values; never round only the cache key while returning a distinguishable result.",
      "Make ordering semantic and explicit: preserve it when output depends on it, or canonicalise both signature and calculation when records are a set.",
      "A changed calculation input must never return a stale cached logical result; include direct miss and unchanged-reuse tests for every advertised entity family.",
      "A presentation-only change must not recalculate logical analysis, rewrite model metadata, create document history or trigger an exact-Part rebuild when a lightweight layer update is sufficient.",
      "Keep logical positions, findings, assignments and stable identities as model output, while diagnostic geometry remains replaceable derived presentation and exact solids remain a Validate/Export concern.",
      "Validate visibility, selection-to-domain identity, one-command history and refresh behavior in a real GUI; FreeCADCmd visibility is not acceptance evidence.",
      "Preserve reviewed semantic parity unless an engineering rule changes explicitly, while keeping oracle parity separate from provenance and project-cleared output status."
    ],
